OL,4,CCampaign to ban London's 'floating'
OL,5,Cbus stops
OL,6,GCampaigners have called for a ban of
OL,7,Gso-called floating bus stops in London.
OL,9,FThe design, which has a cycle lane
OL,10,Fbetween the stop and the pavement, is
OL,11,Fintended to allow bus passengers to
OL,12,Fget on and off safely while cyclists
OL,13,Fcan keep moving.
OL,15,FTransport for London (TfL), which has
OL,16,Ffunded 160 of the stops, says the
OL,17,Flikelihood of being injured by a
OL,18,Fcyclist at a bypass is "very low".
OL,20,FThe Department for Transport says
OL,21,Fschemes should be accessible to all.
